Question: hospital_1: list the distinct positions of all board-certified and licensed physicians. | physician : employeeid , name , position , ssn | department : departmentid , name , head | affiliated_with : physician , department , primaryaffiliation | procedures : code , name , cost | trained_in : physician , treatment , certificationdate , certificationexpires | patient : ssn , name , address , phone , insuranceid , pcp | nurse : employeeid , name , position , registered , ssn | appointment : appointmentid , patient , prepnurse , physician , start , end , examinationroom | medication : code , name , brand , description | prescribes : physician , patient , medication , date , appointment , dose | block : blockfloor , blockcode | room : roomnumber , roomtype , blockfloor , blockcode , unavailable | on_call : nurse , blockfloor , blockcode , oncallstart , oncallend | stay : stayid , patient , room , staystart , stayend | undergoes : patient , procedures , stay , dateundergoes , physician , assistingnurse

Question: hospital_1: how many board-certified and licensed physicians never took any appointment. | physician : employeeid , name , position , ssn | department : departmentid , name , head | affiliated_with : physician , department , primaryaffiliation | procedures : code , name , cost | trained_in : physician , treatment , certificationdate , certificationexpires | patient : ssn , name , address , phone , insuranceid , pcp | nurse : employeeid , name , position , registered , ssn | appointment : appointmentid , patient , prepnurse , physician , start , end , examinationroom | medication : code , name , brand , description | prescribes : physician , patient , medication , date , appointment , dose | block : blockfloor , blockcode | room : roomnumber , roomtype , blockfloor , blockcode , unavailable | on_call : nurse , blockfloor , blockcode , oncallstart , oncallend | stay : stayid , patient , room , staystart , stayend | undergoes : patient , procedures , stay , dateundergoes , physician , assistingnurse
Parse: select count(*) from physician except select t2.name from appointment as t1 join physician as t2 on t1.physician = t2.employeeid where position not in ('Staff Internist')

Question: hospital_1: find the employee ids of all board-certified and licensed physicians and their primary affiliated departments' names. | physician : employeeid , name , position , ssn | department : departmentid , name , head | affiliated_with : physician , department , primaryaffiliation | procedures : code , name , cost | trained_in : physician , treatment , certificationdate , certificationexpires | patient : ssn , name , address , phone , insuranceid , pcp | nurse : employeeid , name , position , registered , ssn | appointment : appointmentid , patient , prepnurse , physician , start , end , examinationroom | medication : code , name , brand , description | prescribes : physician , patient , medication , date , appointment , dose | block : blockfloor , blockcode | room : roomnumber , roomtype , blockfloor , blockcode , unavailable | on_call : nurse , blockfloor , blockcode , oncallstart , oncallend | stay : stayid , patient , room , staystart , stayend | undergoes : patient , procedures , stay , dateundergoes , physician , assistingnurse
Parse: select t1.employeeid, t3.name from physician as t1 join affiliated_with as t2 on t1.employeeid = t2.physician join department as t3 on t2.department = t3.departmentid where position not in ('Staff Internist') and t2.primaryaffiliation = 1

Question: hospital_1: what are the name and primarily affiliated department name of each board-certified and licensed physician? | physician : employeeid , name , position , ssn | department : departmentid , name , head | affiliated_with : physician , department , primaryaffiliation | procedures : code , name , cost | trained_in : physician , treatment , certificationdate , certificationexpires | patient : ssn , name , address , phone , insuranceid , pcp | nurse : employeeid , name , position , registered , ssn | appointment : appointmentid , patient , prepnurse , physician , start , end , examinationroom | medication : code , name , brand , description | prescribes : physician , patient , medication , date , appointment , dose | block : blockfloor , blockcode | room : roomnumber , roomtype , blockfloor , blockcode , unavailable | on_call : nurse , blockfloor , blockcode , oncallstart , oncallend | stay : stayid , patient , room , staystart , stayend | undergoes : patient , procedures , stay , dateundergoes , physician , assistingnurse

Question: hospital_1: what procedures cost less than 5000 and have a trained board-certified and licensed physician? | physician : employeeid , name , position , ssn | department : departmentid , name , head | affiliated_with : physician , department , primaryaffiliation | procedures : code , name , cost | trained_in : physician , treatment , certificationdate , certificationexpires | patient : ssn , name , address , phone , insuranceid , pcp | nurse : employeeid , name , position , registered , ssn | appointment : appointmentid , patient , prepnurse , physician , start , end , examinationroom | medication : code , name , brand , description | prescribes : physician , patient , medication , date , appointment , dose | block : blockfloor , blockcode | room : roomnumber , roomtype , blockfloor , blockcode , unavailable | on_call : nurse , blockfloor , blockcode , oncallstart , oncallend | stay : stayid , patient , room , staystart , stayend | undergoes : patient , procedures , stay , dateundergoes , physician , assistingnurse
Parse: select name from procedures where cost < 5000 intersect select t3.name from physician as t1 where position not in ('Staff Internist') join trained_in as t2 on t1.employeeid = t2.physician join procedures as t3 on t3.code = t2.treatment where position not in ('Staff Internist')
